==English==

===Adjective===

'''deliberate'''

# done on purpose; intentional
#:''He tripped me up deliberately!''
# ''(of a person)'' weighing facts and arguments with a view to a choice or decision; carefully considering the probable consequences of a step; circumspect; slow in determining; as, a deliberate judge or counselor.
#formed with deliberation; well-advised; carefully considered; not sudden or rash; as, a deliberate opinion; a deliberate measure or result.
#Not hasty or sudden; slow.


